        <prompt>The Scopes "Monkey" Trial's significance extended beyond evolution to represent:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">A scientific debate only</option>
            <option letter="b">The broader conflict between modernism and traditionalism</option>
            <option letter="c">Educational funding issues</option>
            <option letter="d">Political party differences</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The 1925 Scopes Trial represented a broader cultural conflict between modernism and traditionalism in 1920s America. While ostensibly about teaching evolution, the trial symbolized deeper tensions between rural religious fundamentalism and urban secular modernism, traditional values and changing social norms, and faith versus science. The trial's extensive media coverage made it a defining moment in this cultural divide.</explanation>
